AI startups are out of control.
Everyone’s cousin is “building the future” by slapping ChatGPT into a shiny wrapper, giving it a brand name like “Rilla,” “Synthia,” or “VibeIQ”, and calling it innovation.

In this video, we dive into one of the most overhyped AI sales startups — a company that records your calls, trains on your voice, and calls it “coaching.” Managers can now “virtually ride along” from anywhere (even skydiving, apparently) while making sure you say “this week’s deal” enough times to meet script complian
